# MinerPulse — strict development rules

## Versioning (mandatory)

- **Product version** (`VERSION.json` → `version`): change **only when the owner explicitly approves** (e.g. "bump version to 1.1.0").
- **Build number** (`VERSION.json` → `build`): increment **after each logical code change** via `node scripts/bump-build.mjs` — **independent of commit/push** (change code → bump build, always).
- After bumping, `sync-version.mjs` runs automatically (via bump script).
- When you do commit, include `build N` in the commit message.
- Tag releases as `v{version}-build{build}`.

## Git workflow (mandatory)

- After each logical change: **bump build first** (see Versioning). Commit and push only when the owner asks or per release workflow — build bump is **not** gated on git.
- Never force-push `main`.
- Never commit secrets (`.tauri/*.key`, `.env`, credentials). Public updater pubkey (`.tauri/*.key.pub`) may be committed when intentionally rotated with config.
- Never commit paths in `.gitignore` (`target/`, `node_modules/`, build artifacts, local-only dirs).

## Code quality

- Minimize scope; no unrelated refactors.
- Rust: business rules in `minerpulse-core`; UI in Svelte; no user-facing strings in Rust (use `ErrorCode` only).
- All UI strings via i18n (`ru`, `en`, `zh-CN`) — no hardcoded text in components.
- Match existing Design System tokens; do not introduce new UI libraries without approval.

## Security and licensing

- **Never** weaken entitlement checks client-side only; subscription tier must remain enforceable server-side.
- **Never** remove or bypass updater signature verification.
- **Never** add code that exfiltrates user data without documented consent.
- **Never** paste unreviewed third-party or local-only reference code into the public tree.

## Forbidden actions (AI agents)

- Do not change `VERSION.json` `version` field without explicit owner request.
- Do not publish private keys or generate keys and commit them.
- Do not disable `createUpdaterArtifacts` or updater pubkey config.
- Do not make the repo public with GPL if LICENSE is proprietary — keep [LICENSE](../LICENSE) consistent.
- Do not claim forks can be disabled on public GitHub — document limits honestly.
- Do not run destructive git commands (`reset --hard`, force push) unless owner explicitly asks.
- Do not skip build bump after completing a logical change.

## Updates and releases

- `releases/update.json` must match `VERSION.json` after each release.
- Update `signature` and `url` only with signed artifacts from `tauri build`.
- Document release steps in [releases/README.md](../releases/README.md).

## When uncertain

- Ask the owner before: version bumps, license changes, new paid-tier rules, removing features, or splitting repos.
